name: Electromagnetism
description:
According to Wikipedia: “Electromagnetism is a branch of physics involving the study of the electromagnetic force, a type of physical interaction that occurs between electrically charged particles. ... At high energy, the weak force and electromagnetic force are unified as a single electroweak force.” In other words, the continuous force field that pushes through earth. (Earth’s aura) So call it. You can see this pattern when you cut an apple in half (2-D) or you can think of it as a hollow doughnut 🍩. 
Medium: Oil/Acrylic on canvas
